The paper deals with the performance analysis of a hybrid-automatic-repeat-request (HARQ) system, which is a communication protocol used in wireless networks. The paper focuses on the queueing characteristics of these systems and investigates the effects of physical layer characteristics on data link layer performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the effective capacity, which is a concept used in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and puts forward non-asymptotic backlog and delay bounds, which are relevant to Performance Analysis (cs.PF).
